Do you have any CS background at all? Down at the level of the ones and zeroes, there's nothing there but primitives: load the value of this variable into this memory location, compare it with the value of a second variable, if it is equal or greater pop the top value off the stack and assign its value to a third value, otherwise jump the instruction pointer to this location... This can be technically fascinating for what it is, but if you're looking for intelligence, it's just a machine. It's a very sophisticated idiot that does exactly what it is told, very very fast.
